The paper discusses a method for evaluating ranking systems, which is a common topic in information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also discusses the user experience and sensitivity to user preferences, which are topics in human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The paper proposes a new method that is theoretically guaranteed to be considerate and have fidelity, which are topics in machine learning (cs.LG) and cryptography (cs.CY).
